      • indexOf

        int indexOf(int x)
        Follows the convention of Arrays.binarySearch(int[], int):
        • If x is contained in this sequence, returns the index of x
        • Otherwise, returns (-insertionPoint - 1)
        See Also:
        Arrays.binarySearch(int[], int)

      • indexNearest

        int indexNearest(int x)
        Index of the value closest to x. If the two closest values are x-C and x+C, returns the index of x+C. If ints is empty, returns -1.

        void continuousIndicesOf(SortedInts xs,

        For each x in xs, the continuous index at which x falls in this sequence. Since xs is sorted, this method may be faster than continuousIndicesOf(Ints, ContinuousIndexArray) in some implementations.
